Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
createTQuantusModelFile(25.10)                  createTQuantusModelFile(25.10)

Name
       createTQuantusModelFile  - Creates the RC model data and stores it in a
       TQuantus model file

Syntax
       createTQuantusModelFile

       [-help]

       -file <rc_model_file_name>

       [-reset]

       Creates the RC model data and stores it in a TQuantus model file.  This
       data  is used by the RC extractor. This command eliminates the need for
       the RC extractor to rebuild the RC models every time it  runs.  It  can
       just use the model data created using this command. Before creating the
       TQuantus model file, ensure the following:

              * QRC techfiles are available

              * Pitch information from the technology LEF file is available

              * All RC corners are set up

       The consistency of the created TQuantus model file is checked using the
       checkTQuantusModelFile command.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes the type and default
              information for each createTQuantusModelFile parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command

              man createTQuantusModelFile.

       -file <rc_model_file_name>
              Writes the created RC model data into a file with the  specified
              file name.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -reset Resets the RC model file.

              Data_type: bool, optional

Example
              * The  following command creates the RC model data and stores it
                in the tQuantus_model.bin file:

                createTQuantusModelFile -file tQuantus_model.bin

